722739f-a.text:
(1)
99th To 100 Street West and Riverside Drive showing residence where Vaughan Kester wrote his first novel,"The Manager of the B&A.",1901. Later on he purchased Gunston Hall,Fairfax County,Virginia,(about
1900),the home of George Mason.
Ref.Who's Who in America 1910-11
New York Times,July 6th,1911.
Vaughan Kester B.Sept.12,1869
D.July 4th,1911.
(2 ) The same.
(3) The same.
(4)  The same.
No Record of Photographer. (Information from Paul Kester
his brother.)
